{"TopicId":144475,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Setting trim by Alt \u002B WASD necessitates loss of control of craft","CreatedByName":"THX1138","CreatedById":113955,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-24T19:35:45Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"THX1138","CreatedById":113955,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-24T19:35:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a better way to set trim than to press Alt \u002B W/A/S/D/Q/E? Trim is set very slowly and I can\u0027t just sit there holding S because then my plane stalls and maybe even goes into a spin (fin has\u00A0overheated and died). I\u0027m forced to keep pressing S for brief pulses but the oscillations have to be carefully controlled or I end up in a spin again.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MachTurtle","CreatedById":153223,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-24T20:38:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wholeheartedly agree, THX.\u00A0 Squad needs to have two key bindings for up and down pitch trim and allow them to be user assignable to either keystrokes or joystick buttons. I believe almost every flight simulator has this key feature implemented.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wjolcz","CreatedById":39636,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-24T20:40:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can trim control surfaces in this game!?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sardia","CreatedById":149922,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-24T21:43:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy don\u0027t you change the key pad assignments? People had the same complaints about the rover wheel controls. Same solution.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"THX1138","CreatedById":113955,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-24T21:57:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222689615\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022144475\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469396605\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022149922\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sardia\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, sardia said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy don\u0027t you change the key pad assignments? People had the same complaints about the rover wheel controls. Same solution.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t understand the solution. If I map W to Num8 it will still do the same thing when I press Alt \u002B Num8 and I\u0027ll lose control of the craft. If I map Alt to #, the same thing. Changing the key assignments doesn\u0027t resolve the problem?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbin vonKerbal","CreatedById":157973,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-24T22:24:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can also use CAPS LOCK \u002B WASD for fine tuning control, which in your case sounds like it would help. Check your authority limiter on whatever control surface you have your pitch assigned to as well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-07-24T22:25:07Z\u0022 title=\u002207/24/2016 10:25  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 24, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Kerbin vonKerbal\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alshain","CreatedById":110959,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-24T23:13:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222689553\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022144475\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469392832\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002239636\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Veeltch\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Veeltch said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can trim control surfaces in this game!?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, if you fly without \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pecan","CreatedById":96332,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-24T23:17:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222689483\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022144475\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469388945\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022113955\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022THX1138\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, THX1138 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a better way to set trim ... because then my plane stalls and maybe even goes into a spin.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave you thought of setting trim - or, *gasp* designing your plane - so that it is flyable before you even take off? \u00A0Any changes then required because of altitude/velocity/fuel-loss should be minimal.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"THX1138","CreatedById":113955,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-25T02:07:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222689697\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022144475\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469402278\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002296332\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Pecan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Pecan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave you thought of setting trim - or, *gasp* designing your plane - so that it is flyable before you even take off? \u00A0Any changes then required because of altitude/velocity/fuel-loss should be minimal.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou don\u0027t know what you\u0027re talking about. There\u0027s nothing wrong with the design of the plane - it\u0027s perfectly flyable -\u00A0but traversing long distances takes a long time and I don\u0027t want to baby sit the plane. I want to leave it with trim set to pull up and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E set to hold prograde so I can do something else but the process of setting trim requires long presses on the keys. I didn\u0027t take off; I deployed the plane from orbit and how am I supposed to know what to set the trim to before I\u0027m in conditions I want it to work in?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Snark","CreatedById":125662,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-25T02:10:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMoving to Gameplay Questions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Red Iron Crown","CreatedById":12858,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-25T02:19:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222689868\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022144475\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469412434\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022113955\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022THX1138\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 minutes ago, THX1138 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI want to leave it with trim set to pull up and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E set to hold prograde so I can do something else...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTrim has no effect when \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E is active.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-25T03:02:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYour only real solution is a TiltProbeCore, I think.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/138791-commercial-break-reap-the-powers-of-the-tiltprobecore%E2%84%A2/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;embedComment=2556877\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-07-25T03:09:32Z\u0022 title=\u002207/25/2016 03:09  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 25, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by bewing\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pecan","CreatedById":96332,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-25T12:45:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222689868\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022144475\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469412434\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022113955\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022THX1138\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, THX1138 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou don\u0027t know what you\u0027re talking about ...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry about that then, I\u0027ll leave you alone and go back to my planes that don\u0027t stall as soon as I hit \u0027S\u0027 or become unflyable just while I\u0027m setting trim. \u00A0Good luck with that self-flying \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E/trim thing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou might like to try ... no, I don\u0027t know what I\u0027m talking about.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OHara","CreatedById":162784,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-14T00:51:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere was what seems to be a good \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/81915-extended-trim/\u0026amp;page=1\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Edesign\u003C/a\u003E to solve this, in a mod for 0.23. \u00A0It gave a way to transfer the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E-controlled steering to the trim settings, so there is continuity when we release \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E. \u00A0I don\u0027t see any current mod implementing it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jarin","CreatedById":71395,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-14T20:54:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat really needs to be done is for the game to recognize mod\u002B\u0026lt;key\u0026gt; as not ALSO pressing \u0026lt;key\u0026gt;. Alt\u002BW should not also give the effect of pressing W by itself. This is interface design 101.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pecan","CreatedById":96332,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-14T22:21:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222717187\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022144475\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221471208070\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002271395\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jarin\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Jarin said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat really needs to be done is for the game to recognize mod\u002B\u0026lt;key\u0026gt; as not ALSO pressing \u0026lt;key\u0026gt;. Alt\u002BW should not also give the effect of pressing W by itself. This is interface design 101.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLucky they incorporated that then. At least on PC - are you on a different system?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alshain","CreatedById":110959,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-14T22:32:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222717187\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022144475\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221471208070\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002271395\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jarin\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Jarin said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat really needs to be done is for the game to recognize mod\u002B\u0026lt;key\u0026gt; as not ALSO pressing \u0026lt;key\u0026gt;. Alt\u002BW should not also give the effect of pressing W by itself. This is interface design 101.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat fact that it already behaves as you suggest is the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it.\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it.\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u0027s problem.\u00A0 What really needs to be done is to make the Trim keys (or for that matter \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EALL KEYS\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E) assignable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-14T22:34:12Z\u0022 title=\u002208/14/2016 10:34  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 14, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Alshain\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jarin","CreatedById":71395,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-15T06:00:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222717286\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022144475\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221471213305\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002296332\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Pecan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, Pecan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLucky they incorporated that then. At least on PC - are you on a different system?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m on Windows 10 and it\u0027s never worked that way for me. It\u0027s a fairly constant problem, really, which I never though to report as a bug. Guess it\u0027s time to investigate...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: I know for a fact that alt\u002Bf12 still registers the f12, so is it just the WASD they exempted? I don\u0027t use trim personally.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-15T06:02:00Z\u0022 title=\u002208/15/2016 06:02  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 15, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Jarin\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}